This strategy identifies equal highs and equal lows - horizontal price levels where multiple swing points cluster within a defined tolerance. These levels represent liquidity pools where stop losses accumulate, making them prime areas for reversals.

How It Works
Equal Highs Detection:

Scans the lookback period for the highest high
Counts how many bars have highs within the tolerance of that level
If 2+ touches exist, an "equal highs" zone is confirmed
Equal Lows Detection:

Scans the lookback period for the lowest low
Counts how many bars have lows within the tolerance of that level
If 2+ touches exist, an "equal lows" zone is confirmed
Entry Logic:

Short Entry: When equal highs exist AND current bar touches/reaches that level
Long Entry: When equal lows exist AND current bar touches/reaches that level
Exit Logic (ATR-Based):

Stop Loss: ATR × Stop Multiplier (default 1.5)
Take Profit: ATR × Target Multiplier (default 2.5)
Settings
Parameter Default Description
Lookback Bars 30 Period to scan for equal levels
Tolerance 5.0 Points within which highs/lows are considered "equal"
ATR Length 14 ATR calculation period
ATR Stop Mult 1.5 Stop distance = ATR × this value
ATR Target Mult 2.5 Target distance = ATR × this value
Session 0830-1500 Trading hours filter
Best Used On
NQ, ES, and other index futures
1-minute to 15-minute timeframes
High-volume sessions (US market hours)
Release Notes
A counter-trend strategy that identifies and trades reversals at Equal Highs (EQH) and Equal Lows (EQL) — institutional liquidity levels where stop-loss orders cluster. The strategy anticipates liquidity grabs followed by price reversals.

Strategy Logic:

This system scans for price levels that have been tested multiple times within a configurable tolerance. These "equal" levels represent liquidity pools that attract institutional order flow:

• Equal Highs (EQH): When price touches the same high level 2+ times, shorts are triggered on the next touch — anticipating a reversal after the liquidity sweep.

• Equal Lows (EQL): When price touches the same low level 2+ times, longs are triggered on the next touch — anticipating a bounce after stops are taken.

Key Features:

• Session Filter (9:45–14:00 ET): Avoids the volatile opening 15 minutes and late-day chop, focusing on the most tradeable hours.

• ATR-Based Risk Management: Dynamic stop-loss (1.5x ATR) and profit target (2.5x ATR) adapt to current market volatility, maintaining a 1.67:1 reward-to-risk ratio.

• Clean Execution: One position at a time, no pyramiding, flat by session end.

Settings:

Parameter Default Description
Lookback Bars 30 Period to scan for equal levels
Tolerance 5.0 pts How close prices must be to count as "equal"
Session 9:45–14:00 Active trading window
ATR Length 14 Volatility measurement period
ATR Stop Mult 1.5 Stop-loss distance
ATR Target Mult 2.5 Take-profit distance
Recommended Use:

• Designed for NQ/MNQ futures on 1-minute or 5-minute charts

• Works on other liquid instruments — adjust tolerance for price scale

• Backtest on your specific market before live trading

Risk Disclosure:

Trading futures involves substantial risk of loss. Past performance does not guarantee future results. This strategy is provided for educational purposes. Always use appropriate position sizing and never risk more than you can afford to lose.
Release Notes
A counter-trend strategy that identifies and trades reversals at Equal Lows (EQL) —
institutional liquidity levels where stop-loss clusters form. When price revisits the
same low 3 or more times within a configurable lookback window, it signals a high-
probability demand zone. The strategy enters long on the next qualified touch,
anticipating a bounce as institutional orders absorb the selling pressure.

---

Strategy Logic

Equal Lows (EQL) represent price levels where sell-stops accumulate below the market.
When price tests the same low repeatedly without breaking down, it signals that buyers
are defending that level. This system scans the last 30 bars for lows within 5 points
of the current low — requiring at least 3 prior touches before a signal is valid. The
more times a level holds, the stronger the institutional interest.

Three filters work together to ensure only the highest-quality setups trigger:

RSI Oversold Filter: Entries only fire when RSI(14) is at or below 40, confirming
that momentum is genuinely depressed at the level rather than price merely drifting
into support.

Rejection Candle Filter: The signal bar must close above its midpoint — meaning price
wicked down into the EQL level but closed back up, showing immediate rejection. This
single-bar confirmation dramatically improves entry timing.

Longs Only: Backtesting across 13 months confirmed that EQL longs carry a statistically
significant edge while EQH shorts do not. This version trades only the long side.

---

Risk Management

Stop Loss: Fixed 10 points below the Equal Low anchor, providing defined risk on every
trade regardless of volatility.

Profit Target: Dynamic, set at 3x ATR(14) above the entry level. Using ATR for the
target rather than a fixed point distance allows the strategy to capture larger moves
during high-volatility sessions while keeping targets realistic during quiet periods.

This creates an asymmetric risk profile — a fixed small loss against a variable larger
gain — which is the foundation of the strategy's edge.

Session Filter: Active 09:45 to 14:00 ET, avoiding the volatile opening 15 minutes
and late-session liquidity decay.

Cooldown: A minimum 3-bar gap between entries on the same level prevents over-trading
a single setup.

---

Settings

Parameter | Default | Description
-------------------|---------|------------------------------------------
Lookback Bars | 30 | Bars scanned for equal low touches
Tolerance | 5 pts | Max distance between lows to qualify
Min Touches | 3 | Prior touches required before signal
Session | 0945-1400 ET | Active trading window
Entry Within | 5 pts | Max distance from anchor to enter
Cooldown Bars | 3 | Min bars between entries on same level
Stop Loss | 10 pts | Fixed points below the EQL anchor
Target Multiplier | 3.0x | Profit target = ATR x multiplier
RSI Filter | ON / 40 | Only enter when RSI(14) <= 40
Rejection Candle | ON | Close must be above bar midpoint
Longs Only | ON | EQL longs only — shorts disabled

---

Recommended Use

Designed for NQ and MNQ futures on the 1-minute chart.
Works on other liquid instruments — adjust tolerance to match the instrument's
typical tick range.
Always backtest on your specific market and time period before live trading.

---

Risk Disclosure

Trading futures involves substantial risk of loss and is not appropriate for all
investors. Past performance is not indicative of future results. This strategy is
provided for educational purposes only. Always use appropriate position sizing and
never risk more than you can afford to lose.
